      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Most organisations rush to write AI policies that end up gathering dust because they are too complex, too vague, or simply disconnected from how people actually work. This lesson walks you through what makes a practical AI usage policy effective, covering the key elements that need to be in place without overwhelming your team with jargon or legal language. You will learn how to identify the specific risks and boundaries that matter most for your context, and how to write clear, actionable guidelines that staff will actually follow. By the end, you will have a straightforward framework you can adapt and implement straight away, whether you are starting from scratch or improving something that already exists.",
